pageTitle: Warriors' start preseason schedule in Los Angeles - SFGate
textBeforeTable: Here's an early look (all times Pacific): The Warriors will fly more than 5,000 miles to play their first six preseason games before hosting their final two at Oracle Arena. They'll spend nearly a week in the Los Angeles area, playing the Clippers and the Lakers at the Staples Center and then meeting the Lakers a second time in Ontario. After sleeping in their own beds for a night or two, the Warriors will wend their way through Des Moines, Iowa; Kansas City, Mo.; and Hidalgo, Texas, for games.
